# ccr exclude-patterns — copy to ~/.config/ccr/exclude-patterns and edit.
#
# One pattern per line. Each is a case-insensitive SUBSTRING matched against a
# session's title and its first prompt. Any session that matches is hidden from
# `ccr` by default (use `ccr -a` or ctrl-a in the picker to see hidden ones).
#
# Blank lines and lines starting with # are ignored.
#
# Examples:
# Generate a diary entry for
# You are an elite PR reviewer
